p (x,y,z)
x - time series
y - dimensionality reduecd representation
z - cluster id

PCA/FA

p(x,y) generative model
p(x | y) likelihood
p(y | x) posterior/mapping to reduced representation

Clustering

p(y,z)
p(y | z) likelihood
p(z | y) posterior/clustering, map reduced representations to clusters

sum over y p(x | y)p(y|z) feed in z, generate example time series

Combine models:

p(x,y,z) = p(x | y) p(y,z)

can compute: log p(x; theta)

Optimization:

p(x,y)
p(y,z)

p(x,y,z)


Visualization:

p(y | x) -> p(x | y)
p(x | z)
